The only official communication I've had so far is an email from Steve Lee, 12 days ago, saying that someone would contact me to answer my questions by the end of the day

Content:

some documentation on what "fungible cluster" means

Author: Alright#0419
Content: #kmdlabs runs one if you want to see an example of how it works

Author: Alright#0419
Content: Basically "one coin, many blockchains"

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content:
@runpaint a fungible chain allows cross chain token migration. a non-fungible chain does not.
basically with a fungible chain, you can migrate tokens from one chain in the cluster to another. We have done extensive testing in #kmdlabs with this

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: this guide may assist in further understanding - https://developers.komodoplatform.com/basic-docs/smart-chains/smart-chain-api/crosschain.html

Author: runpaint#7773
Content: If 2 coins are fungible, does that mean they have to be swapped 1-for-1 and have equal value?  Or can an exchange rate be set?

Author: Alright#0419
Content: they are always 1 for 1 as of right now

Author: Alright#0419
Content: really simple way of thinking about it is that it's 1 coin spread across multiple blockchains

Author: Alright#0419
Content: each blockchain can have a unique purpose or feature

Author: runpaint#7773
Content: Ok but I assume both chains would have to whitelist the other, or else I could just make a billion coin premine and make it fungible with KMD

Author: Alright#0419
Content: It relies on a notary network to keep them fungible with each other. So for example, LABS requires 8 notaries to add a new chain.

Author: Alright#0419
Content: but yes, pretty much. You can add new coins to the supply by adding new chains to the cluster. LABS has a bunch of stuff to limit this though, could try to walk you through it if you're interested

Author: Alright#0419
Content: on LABS at least, it's not as simple as 8 notaries adding a new chain to print a billion new coins

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: they need to share the same ac_cc parameter to be in the same cluster. and migrations  are validated via dPoW, so without notaries to confirm the creation / burn, it wont happen.

Author: runpaint#7773
Content: Does AtomicDEX work on fungible clusters, or is that different

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: not sure what you mean, but if you mean what I think you mean - no.

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: here's a good explanation - https://komodoplatform.com/market-maker-2-overview

Author: ca333#0118
Content: @load listing your coin on atomicDEX-API is free - only listing it in the mobile DEX application for smartphones does cost a "integration" fee.

Author: ca333#0118
Content: @smk762 -  dracocanis ominator all KMD smartchains are supported by atomicDEX

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: yes, I've added a few with electrums in the coins repo to the TUI without issue.

Author: smk762 -  dracocanis ominator#7640
Content: so a fungible cluster could be listed on atomicdex, but the underlying atomic swap tech is not based on fungible clusters.

Author: runpaint#7773
Content: @ca333 is there a list of cluster numbers that are already in use, which I should avoid because other coins are on those clusters?  If there's no need to avoid overlapping cluster numbers, then it seems that the cluster numbers are unnecessary

Author: runpaint#7773
Content: Maybe the Antara Composer system would've told me the cluster number was already taken, if I had chosen a cluster that was already taken.

Author: ca333#0118
Content: We don't enforce "unique" cluster IDs (ac_cc param) since you couldn't launch a second chain to interact with the initial chain. Already "taken" cluster IDs can be found here: https://github.com/KomodoPlatform/komodo/blob/dev/src/assetchains.old - and more infos ref. clusters of chains whose tokens are fungible: https://developers.komodoplatform.com/basic-docs/antara/antara-setup/antara-customizations.html#ac-cc

Author: ca333#0118
Content: Feel free to ping me at any time if something is not clear - thanks!
